Intersection Observer:

Properties of IntersetionObserverEntry:
- boundingClientRect:DOMRectReadOnly -> the whole of the target element.
- intersectionRatio -> intersection-area/boundingClient-area.
- inersectionRect:DOMRectReadOnly -> only the visible part of the target element.
- isIntersecting -> true,when the intersection happens; false, if scrolled back(container/viewport) to top again
- isVisible -> ??????
- rootBounds:DOMRectReadOnly -> by default: viewport; OR you can set it in option
- target -> on whoom the insersection is observed.
- time -> A DOMHighResTimeStamp indicating the time at which the intersection was calculated.
